<subSubSection id="DB8C65393057FFF7FF54FDB8FC316043" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="932936B23057FFF7FF54FDB8FC316043" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FF54FDB8FE95601F" bold="true" box="[199,328,547,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is derived from the Latin “album” (white), referring to the yellowish-white pubescence on body. The compound specific epithet is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB8C65393057FFF7FF54FDF0FBF0611B" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="932936B23057FFF7FF54FDF0FAE260EF" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FF54FDF0FEE960A7" bold="true" box="[199,308,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Remarks</emphasis>
. The general appearance of 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FD1AFDF0FC5860A7" authority="Pérez-Flores &amp; Santos-Silva, 2021" authorityName="Pérez-Flores &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[649,901,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FD1AFDF0FC5860A7" box="[649,901,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Pseudastylopsis albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BAD157DB3057FFF7FC02FDF0FC2C60A7" box="[913,1009,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" rank="species">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC02FDF0FC7660A7" bold="true" box="[913,939,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC2DFDF0FC3760A7" bold="true" box="[958,1002,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FBEBFDF0FF0F608B" authority="Casey, 1913" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FBEBFDF0FA9A60A7" box="[1144,1351,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Leptostylus batesi</emphasis>
Casey, 1913
</taxonomicName>
. However, the body shape, and especially the prothoracic shape is that of 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FB8EFD14FB0D608B" authorityName="Dillon" authorityYear="1956" box="[1053,1232,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FB8EFD14FB0D608B" box="[1053,1232,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Pseudastylopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, the mesoventral process is wider than mesocoxal cavity in 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FC92FD28FCBC60EF" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1913" box="[769,865,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC92FD28FCCC60EE" box="[769,785,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC8DFD28FCBC60EF" box="[798,865,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while it is distinctly narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FB4EFD28FAE460EF" authorityName="Pérez-Flores &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[1245,1337,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FB4EFD28FB3360EE" box="[1245,1262,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FB6FFD28FAE460EF" box="[1276,1337,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="932936B23057FFF7FF54FD4CFBF0611B" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">
In 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FF7AFD4CFE4160D3" authorityName="Dillon" authorityYear="1956" box="[233,412,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FF7AFD4CFE4160D3" box="[233,412,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">Pseudastylopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FE3EFD4CFDD160D3" authority="Pérez-Flores &amp; Santos-Silva, 2021" authorityName="Pérez-Flores &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[429,524,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FE3EFD4CFE6360D2" box="[429,446,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FE5CFD4CFDD160D3" box="[463,524,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BAD157DB3057FFF7FD85FD4CFDA960D3" box="[534,628,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" rank="species">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FD85FD4CFDED60D3" bold="true" box="[534,560,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FDD2FD4CFDB060D3" bold="true" box="[577,621,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FC1DFD4CFA4560D3" authority="nelsoni Linsley &amp; Chemsak, 1995" authorityName="Linsley &amp; Chemsak" authorityYear="1995" box="[910,1432,726,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nelsoni" subSpecies="nelsoni">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC1DFD4CFC4260D2" box="[910,927,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC23FD4CFB8160D3" box="[944,1116,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">nelsoni nelsoni</emphasis>
Linsley &amp; Chemsak, 1995
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FF04FD60FD776137" authority="Linsley &amp; Chemsak, 1995" authorityName="Linsley &amp; Chemsak" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,682,762,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nelsoni" subSpecies="australis">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FF04FD60FF756136" box="[151,168,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FF2BFD60FEAE6137" box="[184,371,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">nelsoni australis</emphasis>
Linsley &amp; Chemsak, 1995
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="54964D313057FFF7FD74FD60FBDF6137" authority="(Schaeffer, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[743,1026,762,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudastylopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pini">
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FD74FD60FD256136" box="[743,760,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A1E2EAA03057FFF7FC9BFD60FCE96136" box="[776,820,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="187">pini</emphasis>
(Schaeffer, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs especially by the elytral pubescent pattern (see photographs on 
<bibRefCitation id="F7074B433057FFF7FDD8FC84FD34611B" author="Bezark, L. G." box="[587,745,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" refId="ref6029" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2020 a) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World. New World Cerambycidae Catalog. Available from: http: // bezbycids. com / byciddb / wdefault. asp? w = n (Last accessed 22 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">
Bezark 2020 
<bibRefCitation id="F7074B433057FFF7FD4EFC84FD34611B" author="Lingafelter, S. W. &amp; Monne, M. A. &amp; Nearns, E. H." box="[733,745,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="187" refId="ref6451" refString="Lingafelter, S. W., Monne, M. A. &amp; Nearns, E. H. (2020) Online Image Database of Cerambycoid Primary Types of the Smithsonian Institution. Available from: http: // SmithsonianCerambycidae. com / (Last accessed 22 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, and Lingafelter et al. 2020).
</paragraph>
